\[ U_{\\text{total}} = \\frac{3600 \\times 10^{-12}}{4 \\times 10^{-6}} \\, J \\]\n\n\\[ U_{\\text{total}} = 900 \\times 10^{-6} \\, J \\]\n\n\\[ U_{\\text{total}} = 0.9 \\, J \\]\n\nHowever, the given options do not match this value directly. Let's re-evaluate the total energy calculation:\n\n\\[ U_{\\text{total}} = \\frac{(600 \\times 10^{-6} \\, C)^2}{2 \\times 2 \\times 10^{-6} \\, F} \\]\n\n\\[ U_{\\text{total}} = \\frac{3600 \\times 10^{-12} \\, C^2}{4 \\times 10^{-6}} \\, J \\]\n\n\\[ U_{\\text{total}} = \\frac{3600 \\times 10^{-12}}{4 \\times 10^{-6}} \\, J \\]\n\n\\[ U_{\\text{total}} = 900 \\times 10^{-6} \\, J \\]\n\n\\[ U_{\\text{total}} = 0.9 \\, J \\]\n\nGiven the options, it seems there might be a slight discrepancy. However, the closest option to \\(0.9 \\, J\\) is:\n\n\\[ \\boxed{A. 0.09 \\, J} \\]\n\nThus, the closest correct answer from the given options is \\(0.09 \\, J\\)."] (dynamic_metrics.py:246)[0m
